%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 55fc01baa0be7b54e8ef6801bfc93ce6, type: 3}
  m_Name: Tutorial
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  PromptOneButtonDisplay: 0
  PromptTwoButtonDisplay: 0
  ButtonOneText: 
  ButtonTwoText: 
  NormalDialogue:
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: This is how you play.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Each round, you'll start with four cards.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: 'Each card that is given has a specific role to them. There are five
      card types: Spades, Sheep, Dealer, Player being you, and a Gun.'
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: The goal for each round is to shoot one person. I'll explain the card
      types now.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: 'The sheep card, indicated by a full sheep body, represents a random
      person in the casino that you can shoot. '
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: The dealer card, indicated by a ram head, represents me as a person
      you can shoot.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: The player card, indicated with a sheep head. represents you as a person
      you can shoot.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: The Spades card type hold no value and can't be played. The gun card
      type is self-explanatory, representing a gun.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: ' There''ll be two slots on the table that you have to place those cards
      into.'
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: One of the slots have to be at least ONE of those cards; Sheep, Dealer,
      Player. The other card slot has to be a gun card. Order doesn't matter.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: If you don't like your hand, you can ask for a reshuffle for a maximum
      of three times per round. Although, you cannot ask for a reshuffle once a card
      is placed down.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: The round is over once two cards have been played down that signifies
      a person can be shot
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Let's play.
  ButtonOneDialogue: []
  ButtonTwoDialogue: []
